## Calendar Provider

Where Claude should put showing reminders and other calendar events for me.

CALENDAR_PROVIDER: <google | outlook | lofty | skip>

- `google`: Use the Google Calendar MCP. Buyer gets an email invite directly from Google.
- `outlook`: Use the Microsoft 365 connector. Beta in v1 of Phase 2; verify before relying on it.
- `lofty`: Use Lofty's built-in calendar tasks. Always works, no extra setup. Limitation: text-only, no map links or HTML in the reminder, and the buyer will not get an invite from Lofty (Claude will email the buyer separately with an .ics attached).
- `skip`: No calendar event will be created. The Lofty showing-log note is still written, and the buyer still gets an .ics by email.

See `references/calendar_routing.md` for the routing rules.

